Roger,

Unfortunately I don&#39;t.  One way to convert Surface Chemkin files is to 
edit them to make them look like gas-phase mechanisms, convert them to 
.cti format, then edit the .cti file to turn them back into surface 
mechanisms.  It&#39;s a bit cumbersome, but can actually be done in just a 
few minutes.  This is how I created the input file for catalytic 
combustion on platinum, for example.

Of course, it wouldn&#39;t be so hard to write an &quot;sk2cti&quot; program, since 
it would just be a modification of the existing code to convert 
gas-phase mechanism files.  If anyone is interested, the relevant files 
are in Cantera/src/converters.  Take a look at CKParser.cpp and 
CKReader.cpp.

Dave



